==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cannelure
<hw>Can"ne*lure</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧n"n⟦esl⟧*l⟦usl⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., fr. <ets>canneler</ets> to groove.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>A groove in any cylinder; specif., a groove around the cylinder of
an elongated bullet for small arms to contain a lubricant, or around the
rotating band of a gun projectile to lessen the resistance offered to
the rifling. Also, a groove around the base of a cartridge, where the
extractor takes hold.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Can"ne*lured</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cannery</ent>⟦br⟧
